      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Landmark cases demonstrate this principle at work, such as *Griswold v. Connecticut*, which protected a right to marital privacy. Another critical example is *Lawrence v. Texas*, which struck down laws criminalizing private, consensual sexual conduct, safeguarding personal autonomy. Furthermore, cases related to the right to privacy under the Fourteenth Amendment have shown how this doctrine protects intimate life choices from government intrusion. These examples illustrate the court's use of due process to define and defend unenumerated personal liberties.",
      "source": "target",
